1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,610
The quality of your AI output is

2
00:00:01,650 --> 00:00:03,350
determined by the quality of your input.

3
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:06,580
Most sales teams give AI generic prompts

4
00:00:06,620 --> 00:00:07,690
and get generic output.

5
00:00:08,420 --> 00:00:09,580
Write a follow-up email.

6
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:11,230
Summarize this call.

7
00:00:11,780 --> 00:00:12,890
Draft a proposal.

8
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:15,590
The output is technically correct and

9
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:16,850
completely forgettable.

10
00:00:17,660 --> 00:00:19,340
Good prompting in a sales context is

11
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:19,800
different.

12
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:21,780
It includes the buyer's specific

13
00:00:21,830 --> 00:00:22,250
problem.

14
00:00:22,870 --> 00:00:24,510
The language they used to describe it.

15
00:00:25,020 --> 00:00:26,380
The objection they raised and the

16
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:27,380
context behind it.

17
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,810
The outcome they said they needed and

18
00:00:29,870 --> 00:00:31,130
the timeline they gave.

19
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,590
When you give AI that context, the

20
00:00:33,650 --> 00:00:35,720
output sounds like it was written by

21
00:00:35,790 --> 00:00:36,830
someone who was in the room.

22
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,070
Because in a sense, it was.

23
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:41,710
Prompt engineering is not a technical

24
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:42,070
skill.

25
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,880
It is a sales skill.

26
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:46,840
The reps who learn it will outperform

27
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:47,840
the ones who do not.

28
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:49,820
Follow A-Gent to build it.
